{"id":31947,"date":"2019-06-10T12:44:02","date_gmt":"2019-06-10T08:44:02","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=31947"},"modified":"2023-10-05T01:02:27","modified_gmt":"2023-10-04T21:02:27","slug":"ghirah-allah-loves-and-hates","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/06\/10\/ghirah-allah-loves-and-hates\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Gheerah: Protective jealousy that Allah loves and hates"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201c<strong>Among protective jealousy is what Allah loves and hates. As for what Allah loves, it is jealousy when there is probable cause. As for what Allah hates, it is jealousy without probable cause.<\/strong>\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: Sunan Ibn Ma\u0304jah 1996<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <strong><em>Sahih<\/em><\/strong> (authentic) according to Al-Albani<\/p>\n<p>Al-Sindi said, \u201cProtective jealousy with probable cause is suspicion of corruption, meaning, if there are signs of corruption in a situation, acting upon necessary jealousy is praiseworthy. As for when it is acted upon without any sign, acting upon it is blameworthy as it involves accusing Muslims of evil without evidence.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: H\u0323a\u0304shiyat al-Sindi\u0304 1\/515<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0647\u064f\u0631\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0631\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0645\u064e \u0645\u0650\u0646\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0652\u063a\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0631\u064e\u0629\u0650 \u0645\u064e\u0627 \u064a\u064f\u062d\u0650\u0628\u0651\u064f \u06